<item>
            <title>[SOLR-753] CoreDescriptor holds wrong instance dir for single core</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-753</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;for single core ,the  CoreDescriptor is instantiated with the following code&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;CoreDescriptor dcore = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; CoreDescriptor(cores, &quot;&quot;, cfg.getResourceLoader().getInstanceDir());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and the reload in CoreContainer#create(CoreDescriptor dcore) has a snippet as follows&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;File idir = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; File(loader.getInstanceDir(), dcore.getInstanceDir());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which will make the idir value something like &quot;solr/solr/&quot; which is wrong&lt;/p&gt;


